        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 9:04PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 903 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
New Baltimore, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Clemens, New Baltimore, Richmond, Algonac, Romeo, Sterling
Heights, Marine City, Clinton Township, Harsens Island, Macomb
Township, Utica, New Haven, Washington, Anchorville, Adair, Shelby
Township, Ray Center, Fair Haven, Stoney Creek Metro Park, and Pearl
Beach.

People attending Jimmy Johns Field  should seek safe shelter
immediately!
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
